what is a Hendiadys?
A Hendiadys is a type of neurodegenerative disease that affects the liver and kidneys. It's characterized by persistent, recurrent inflammation in both the liver and small intestine which leads to chronic damage over time due to its long-term survival rate being low compared with other forms of cancer. The exact cause of Hendiadys disease is still unknown but it has been linked to a variety of genetic, environmental, and immunological factors that contribute to the development of this condition.
